attributes.magic: PE32 executable (GUI) Intel 80386, for MS Windows

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a stealer malware. It dynamically resolves a large number of APIs to obfuscate its capabilities. The malware performs extensive system reconnaissance, gathering user information, hardware details (via `__cpuid`), and a list of installed software by enumerating the `SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Uninstall` registry key. Its primary function is to steal sensitive data, including credentials and cookies from web browsers (targeting `Login Data`, `Cookies`, `Web Data` files) and cryptocurrency wallets (searching for `wallet.dat`). It uses `CryptUnprotectData` to decrypt browser data and SQLite APIs to parse the database files. The stolen information is then exfiltrated over HTTP POST requests. A mutex (`8724643052`) is used to ensure only one instance of the malware runs at a time.
